
                                            The 17-year-old from Bishop Lavis is the youngest contestant in the competition.
                                         CAPE TOWN - A Cape Town teenager has described how a popular singing competition in the country changed her life.  Seventeen-year-old Paxton Fielies from Bishop Lavis is the youngest contestant in the competition.  She is currently in the top four of this year's Idols South Africa.  “I’ve learned a lot about me as an artist and I’ve learned a lot. Going from a cover artist who gets 200 to 300 views [on YouTube] to somebody who is on Idols SA with millions of people watching, that is amazing.” WATCH: Top 4 Reveal: A true House diva 